<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 5:26PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Roanoke, southeastern Craig and southwestern Botetourt Counties
through 600 PM EDT...
At 525 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Castle, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Troutville...
New Castle...
Catawba...
Fincastle...
Nace...
Laymantown...
and Daleville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Seek shelter inside a building.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
